content: Won't work with current phones/OS. Before that, this was my go to app for years
This is simply the best To do app I have used. Would have been more happy if there was an integration with Samsung or Google calender.
Paid this guy after using free version for years. Should have paid you earlier. Thanks this is a really good app, well done.
Been using it for years. The best notification app out there. A reminder can be added for any combination.
This is a reason to have a cell phone all by itself! If I didn't have this app nothing would get done. I especially like that I was able to customize it to how and what I wanted and needed.
Awful
It was exactly what I was looking for and many other programs have some of the features but this is the only one that combines them all.

This is a great task manager / to do list. It's easy to add tasks and lists them concisely making it easy to see what's coming up. The pop-up reminder option makes them a "can't miss". Not easily overlooked like the notification bar can be. It also offers more advanced task repeat options than many other apps. Great app all around. I've used this app for 8+ years and will continue to.
Suddenly in my fifties the mind can't multitask as well. Lol So I bought this app to handle projects and planning. It's excellent and if you need a task planner highly recommended!
I've been using this app since 2012. It's still my go-to app for task management. I've never found anything that suits me better.
Signs of lazy developer, ugly UI, keeps updating unnecessary stuffs. LAZY!!!

This app is EXACTLY what I was looking for. I have ADD and I am a single mom so I am quite scatterbrained. 😆 I didn't need anything complex - I just needed something simple that would remind me. This app has a widget you can put on your screen that shows you your list, so everytime I look at my phone I see it. Also LOVE that you can customize the widget to have a clear background so I can still see my screen saver through it. (It's the little things.) Perfect. Simple, effective, to the point.

This is the best Task reminder ever !!! I have used it for more than 5 years and are very satisfied with this app. I have had 2 issues and mailed Mike about it, and it has been promptly fixed. I can strongly recommend this app if you have a lot of things you need to do at a certain time or date in the future, in some hours or a date several years in the future, just one time o repeated every month/day/year or whatever schedule in the future.     (I give it more than 5 starts :-)  )
I don't generally like to give 5 stars, but this app just deserves it. I use it all the time to manage info that is important to me.
Perfect app for grad school. Definitely worth the money.
Very nice and usefully app. Thanks. 🙂

updated recently crashed the app. had important dates an reminders on it. cant go back in app. quite annoying. Please can this issue be fixed!! Really dissapointed. Been using this app for years its the best one for me. Please please fix the bug. I uninstalled the app and then reinstalled fresh copy having the same issue.
Very useful app to stay on top of all kinds of tasks

I'm a software developer (39 years), but not Android. This is a nicely written app. I like the interface, it's pretty intuitive. Nice docs and good support. For less than the price of a pint, the pro version is a no brainer. This is a keeper. I'll add to this when I've used it in anger for a few months.
Cannot live without this app.
Excellent tool. The only thing I would change is the Icon desing to make it cooler and fix it to change the stuffs google calendar once you change in the app. Other than that, a thumb up!

Hello developpers of this genius app :) I am a fan of android since 6 years and today I post my first comment ever. I love your app (I bought the pro version) which is the best I tested on play store to allow organisation using ToodleDo + a calendar view. I just have a big problem for me : When I create a note for exemple with a start date at today and a due date in 1 week, in the calendar view, I don't understand why this task is not displayed each day starting and for the 7 next days. It's really a problem when we want to create a task with a range of several days (to set holidays for example) I tested several options (repeat tasks, etc) but I don't find a solution to this problem. Please help me, this is really important for me (and probably for other users) Thanks in advance

One error is in pro version that when filter is set at Hide Completed task, 
even it shows Completed Task in subtask, but such problem is occurred in 
Light version

Great app for tasks! Updated to 5 stars because they added complete and 
snooze functionality from notification window. Can't ask for for anything 
else from this app!
Precisely what I need

I know that some people like this app and It has some good qualities. But the "fixed reminder" as the default reminder is a deal breaker in a bad way. It means the reminder will pop up immediately after I enter the task. Although it has another option as "relevant to the due day" for the reminder, you hace to manually change it each time you enter a task and set the reminder, which makes it very clumsy. I did go through all of the setrings and see some allowance for customization, but not that one. So I won't use this app for most of my tasks although I paid for it.

Feature rich!  This can do everything you want in a to-do app.  It has a billion settings to accommodate anybody's taste and functions; and their all documented on the dev's website.  Outstanding!  Well worth the purchase price.
Makes my life easy
The popup reminder functionality is buggy. Sound started going off and no popup to stop it. Had to restart my phone to get it to stop sounding the alarm....
Perfect reminder notifier for us busy people, and the customization is full featured. from week to, day to hour, minutes to even to seconds. like I said its perfect!

Ecstatic to FINALLY have the simplicity of an efficient (and most of all EFFECTIVE) tool to plan, schedule and be reminded of life's daily activities, appointments and tasks. Does not take over your phone (like so many of the other Apps both Android & Apple). Does not slow down the phone. Love it! Simple, elegant "get-it-at-a-glance" design. Good job!
I am using it for 3-4 years every day and love it. Needs auto backup list and settings or user and password or on a cloud and its perfect. Simple and clean
Backing up to phone or SD card does not work have lost content several times. Unable to backup to cloud or Dropbox
Would like to see an option for automatic backup to cloud specifically Dropbox. Thanks
I use this for my household chores list. It's the best!
The new widget looks great! Thank you.

I've been using this app for 4 years now, so I decided I wanted to try something new and different. Well I tried about 6 of the other most popular task managers. They all sucked compared to this one especially when it comes to customization. So I'm back. (Never really left.)
It looks nice app but not importing XML files
best app ever
I love this app just wish it would sync with Google or save everything to your phone so when you get a new one everything transfers over. It's dumb when you lose everything and have to re-enter it

I tried several todo and reminder apps. This is my favorite. I have used it for 5 years.  I like the categories, snoozing and widget. I use it for chores, shopping lists, important things and just taking notes. Also fully supported and kept up to date!
Love it! been after a new to do list app for ages and this is spot on! 10/10
Task Manager
Great
A must have for task thank you
I have been using this app for years and it has never disappointed me.

If you found this app, you are lucky. I tried Anydo, Todoist, Keep, Wunderlist and nearly every other highly rated to do list / task manager app and I like this one the best. And best of all, no subscription like the others. If new people keep on buying this app, the developer will likely continue to improve this app. It's not as "pretty" as the above noted apps but it is as good or better than any of them and you pay a one time fee only. Relatively comprehensive yet easy to use. Buy it!!!
Best productivity task app. Had it for years and it keeps getting better
Fast, flexible, lots of features. Recurring tasks and alarms exceptionally flexible.

I've been using this app for 4 years and still loving it, especially as it keeps getting better & better. It does everything I want & need it to do to keep my life organized and on track. In fact, it does a whole lot more, too, but I don't currently need those features. Customer service is also "5 star." Thanks!
Very useful
I tried a lot of similar apps but this one has it all and has lots of customization. The repeatedly no tasks are very powerful. Nice improvements lately also.
Customization features are awesome
Please update UI.
Great apps

I've been using this app for a few years now, and it's still a remarkable app. I can't imagine my life without it. I used to use the good-ol' fashioned calendar and pencil method to remind myself of personal bills, tasks for around the house, etc. Not any more. Thank you! It was worth every penny.
This is a great app for keeping track of everything I do on a daily basis, particularly recurring tasks. It has a user friendly interface & many display options. I highly recommend it.

I wrote about the Lite app mentioning that this was the best Task Manager hands down.  In my Lite review, I mentioned about the easy transition from the WebOS Platform.  In that, I mentioned that I was looking for a full screen notification.  Little did I know that this functionality was always there.  I've since recently upgraded to the Pro version because $3 and change is worth having the import function as often as I have to format my devices and re-install due to crapware loading junk.  ToDo List Task Manager still proves to be the best app of its kind.  People may make remarks about its appearance, but in all honesty, what's more important?  Looking pretty, or getting the job done.  At the end of the day, I know what I want.  I'm running this on an HTC EVO 4G LTE and use the 4x1 Widget on my home screen just underneath the sense clock.  No title, transparent, only showing task names and due dates.  Looks good enough to me!  UPDATE: I've seen the update and Mike's Workshop is stepping up the aesthetics of this program up a serious notch! I'm now running this on an HTC One e8 and again, no complaints aside from not being able to give this program 6 stars.  All the best!
Best alternative to Outlook on my PC.
The best task to do at you can find on the market!    GUARANTEED!!!
Useful app
With the latest update the app is much easier to read on the screen. I like the new layout that has been used as readability is better and you don't have to look hard at what you want to type.

I've been using this app for a really, really long time and absolutely love it! It helps me remember and prioritize one time and reoccurring task. It’s very robust, some highlights are: widget settings, sorting, filtering, alarm options, repeat options, auto backups, customize layout, fonts, priorities, calendar view, search, etc. If all that isn’t enough, you can also use it with the web portal app Toodledo to sync and add or edit task online.

All other apps are too basic and can have their reminder notifications swiped away, never to be heard from again. Not good. If something isn't done, you need to be reminded. This app does it the best. Great options!
Best app in standalone mode. Just can't change the destination to a folder in the SD card. Lost all my tasks after a phone format. Had the backup been there in SD card, I could have recovered it.
Been using this app for a while now and I love it however, I'd like to see the start date as an option for the widget...
Excedllent app, but Import/Export menu does not functoning in Android 5. Can it will be fixed???

Love it because it has alarm you can set with snooze so the alarm repeated until you mark task as Completed.  I use the pop up notification.  No other task manage/to do list offers this. I wish the app could seamlessly share my tasks across my devices.

I've been using your app for years, love everything about it except one thing; it's about time you give it a face lift... maybe a new material design would do, the UI is getting really old & unattractive, I hope you take this very seriously. Your competitors are doing a great job at this, the temptation is high... ;)
Very good app. I use this for all of my to do.
Everything seems to be up in the air at this time.

The screenshots may give the impression that this may not be the prettiest task manager to look at but it has very powerful features & works flawlessly. Setting up repeat & alarmed tasks is intuitive as the app displays its understanding of your entries in a review before you save so you know you've set them up completely properly. Brilliant. Great also for annual reminders such as insurances, membership expiries. etc. Repeating advance reminders can be set up to remind you every day, many days before an event is due so you can get focused long before the day of an event & it will keep on reminding you as often as you ask it to (nagging) Worth the money if you want to do things properly.  Note for developer : Please add a feature for ticked tasks to be sent to the bottom of the listing. It's a little distracting for them to remain amongst the main to-do list when actually they have been completed

I'm am old school Franklin planner and Palm task user, both of which I liked.  Nothing I tried for Android was close until this.  It is very, very customizable so you can make it your own in terms of display and sorting and backup.  I like the synch to Toodledo but wish for synch to Google tasks.  Nothing not to love for me.  I don't use subtasks so don't miss those.  I only wish that in-process tasks had a unique check box image. Thanks, Mike.
Love it!
Simply the best

This one stands above the all the rest but there is one item that would make it even better. Can you integrate a seamless way to sync with Google tasks. That way the tasks I enter here would show up on my calendar's to do list. I would rate it 10 stars if it could do that. I know you list a way in the Q&A, but that is not simple nor practical.
Lots of customization and options.
Turn Quiet time  does not work.
Lots of great features.  Great customer service...mentioned an issue with an update and they resolved it quickly!
Use this for many years! Really good! To be the best it should have a claud sync (Dropbox or Google Drive). Please make this available. Toodledo is not the same!

I needed something that managed my today and my next six months. Simplicity for today and detail for the far flung! It has it in spades, an earth digger to be precise. I'm one of the more discerning Play purchasers, by philosophy rather than purse... I paid for the full app, and I don't even need those features.  My gripes come from the fact that this is not more like the old Palm OS, hardly fair... So that's between me and the boss. I once had 16 to do apps on my phone, I have one - the best one by a mile.

The backup user interface is not intuitive. I lost some of my tasks. I went to settings then backed up application settings, thinking that my tasks are also backed up, then I uninstalled app.  When I reinstalled it later, I went to settings to restore my tasks. But it only restored settings not tasks. To backup tasks manually you need to go to a completely different menu in this app, which is not very intuitive. These things should be in the same place. Other than this point, the app is very good.
Ive looked at other to do and nothing can compare to its usefulness like this to do list.  Worth every penny

Works smoothly. Many features and customization options, from appearance to filters to priority system to many options for alerts--which is super helpful. I continue to try various task managers (different projects, shared lists, etc), and this one has remained my primary task manager for several years now!
The most efficient widget
Love this app, have used it for quite a while. To me,  the best there is.  Lots of convenient options

I'm a list maker and I like an app that has all of what I need and no bloat that I don't need. This one hits the bullseye. I've moved it from the original phone to 2 newer ones ... I'll keep moving it because it's a great app. Recurring events, alarms, relative and fixed dates, categories, priorities, and i've yet to check out sub-tasks but I'm sure they'll be awesome too. Dev. had always answered my questions. Grateful and loyal user.
I find this  application very useful.  It's not complicated and has all the features I need. It's there when I need it,  not hiding somewhere.

This is one of the most feature filled todo apps I have found. It has so many customizations that some may get lost in the settings or forget how they changed a setting. I love being able to have this much control. This update resolved many of the issues I had. It doesn't sync directly with Google task, but I like that I can easily export data and print out or save to my PC. I would like to see an option to rename a filter (instead of having to create new filter and then deleting old filter).
Like  this ToDo / Task manager, but it is missing one cruicle feature - there is no caldav sync.
Next to the phone, this is one of the most useful apps I have.
Excellent for organizing my tasks.

I've tried every to do list app available and wasted a bunch of money, but no more.  By far one of the best apps I've ever purchased. I had a few questions before I purchased and the developer answered via email instantly.

ToDo List Task Manager -Pro entry makes entry fast. Need to change that due date? Changing info is fast. Need to just type out a few words because someone needs you...NOW? This app allows it. Need to swap dates because you never complete anything on time? Easy. Am loving the new monthly calendar view for quick review of tasks.  Widget control for fonts and filters before laying it on are unsurpassed. This app is ahead of the pack.
Nearly perfect

Fantastic app!  Love the repeat tasks and reminder alarm!  I use it for something as simple as remembering everyday to give my kids their vitamins in the morning to reminding myself to schedule an annual doctor's appointment every November!
At last the perfect task app. After astrids byout :-( and trying LOTS of task apps I've found the one I will always use. Highly customisable to your needs. Decent widget too.

I used to have the lite version about 2 years ago. Switched to Astrid coz it's free with backup and restore options. Now that Astrid is shutting down, I tried to look for the best alternative. Probably installed every todo app in Play Store. This app has improved greatly since I last used it. Finally bought the Pro version so I can import my backups. Really worth every cent, and cheaper than most todo apps out there. Perfect recurring task options and this is probably the only one with an hourly recurrence.
Need a Pin Lock feature.
APP
I have never been able to find a list / task app that had all the functions especially in alarms notification that I wanted until now,....! A big thank you very well designed
Fully featured to-do manager. Intuitive interface is simple and comprehensive. Only thing missing is it doesn't sync with google tasks directly. Uninstalling to try an app that does for a while.

This is the most useful app around with the most features available. I don't use all of them but having repeating alarms is critical for me. Sometimes I don't hear my phone when the first reminder goes off. That's why I always set my alarms to sound every 30 minutes, every hour, two hours, etc. No other app has this feature. And if I did hear it but just want to postpone the task, I can snooze it for whatever time in the future I want. I've tried other apps because, as W Lin  stated, this UI looks so dated. The need to have repeating alarms keeps me using this app. If I could make one little request...please update look and feel of this app WITHOUT losing any of it's features!

I have used this app for over a year. I upgraded to pro a few months ago. I have used almost every task manager "to-do list" app on the market and can say that this one is by far the best, hands down. No, I'm no employee or relative. Lol. I almost never write reviews. But after I emailed the developer about a problem I had (after searching online) and he replied with the solution only 3 MINUTES LATER, I had to add my review! Props to the Developer! The app is very flexible and versatile; the best out there.

Love everything about the app EXCEPT the esthetics of the UI.  It just looks dated, like it's stuck on XP when everyone has moved on to 7.  Icon looks kind of bad too.  However, when it comes to a Todo app, what's most important is usability and features.  Here, this app has got it made!!  Features are spectacular and after struggling with multiple apps, this was the only one that satisfied my needs.
This is a great list & appointment task keeper. A few to many thing to set up if you want colors & a way to change almost everything to this app. But is great for learning the easy it is.
Feature rich and extremely customizable. Thanks!

I have installed & studied probably the top 15 apps of this type in detail and this is one of the best along with DGT GTD which has similar features. This app is virtually faultless and syncs with Toodledo. I was a little disappointed that it didn't include a simple notebook where I could list all the jobs which were not urgent and could be done anytime, as is possible in Toodledo,but figured out a simple work round so I couls see them at all times. The tasks which have a definite due date I  prioritised -1 to +2 and the non urgent tasks were  categorised priority 3 in Toodledo. Two separate  widgets  were then used for this app. One is sorted on due date and puts all the timed jobs in chronological order. The other widget is sorted on priority and because the non urgent tasks are priority 3, the widget lists the non urgent tasks at the top of the widget list before then listing the due date ones. By using 2 off 4 x 2 widgets both lists are on my phone's home screen.
Great features!!  Does virtually everything I need a task manager to do. I've abandoned my desktop solution as this app is so much better.  I use it every day!!
The app is very good and works well except the alarm repeat function does not work irrespective of the time I set on the Samsung galaxy S2.
I use it everyday and I will not change.
Great program with lots of features.
Really like the UI and what you can do with it in terms of filtering of tasks.  However, really really miss sub tasks. Will keep with one of the other Toodledo 3rd party apps for the moment.
I used ghe free one now the paid this is great app keep up the good work
In my job there are hundreds of repeatable tasks every year. With this app I never miss one! I love it.

Have had the Pro version for several months and overall agree that this is the best out there.  However, within the last couple of weeks it has been crashing (through a forced close) multiple times a day.  Was 5 stars, down to 3-4 stars for me until the crashing issue is resolved.

and I've tried them all!  This app has everything I was looking for in a task app... and my "must have" list was very long!  To make it even better, there's a sister app that allows you to sync with Toodledoo (free & paid services) online.  Now you have your task list on your mobile device, the web, your iCal and your web browser!  Now that's priceless!
This is a great app that helps me stay on top of the tasks I need to get done. I HIGHLY recommend it! ~ Samsung Galaxy Nexus
This app is useless PLEASE I WOULD LIKE MY MONEY BACK

Constant license checking... Annoying if no connection...  Are developers making this product for themselves or for customer. Please fix...   paradigm shift   Though seems to be great app... I even purchased. But
Love it! Helps me stay organized on the go. I've tried others and this is the best I've found.
I've used this app with my Evo for about a year. Really awsome. Highly recommend it.

This used to be a great app until he changed it to having to connect to Google Play all the time for “license verification.”  Now if you are in an area without an active data connection (much of the world) it locks up.  He says you can back button to continue use, but that only works some of the time once or twice, then you have to Kill the app and it is not usable until the next time you have a data connection to Google.  Just when I need my checklist the most, out in the middle of  nowhere, the darn thing dies.  Grrrrr...    Surely there is a better way to prevent pirating the app then having to be connected to Google Play all the time. PS: This is with a fully paid copy.

Far too many applications promise one thing, and deliver nothing of reckognisable merit. This, however, does exactly as it says on the tin: a powerful TODO manager with a good set of features and widgets. It communicates with Executive Assistant, allows for filtering, reminders, priorities, notes, progress, and (limited) workflow handling.  The user interface is clean, with font size handling allowing one to circumvent the usual "too big by far" habit of most Android applications. Date formats can be set, proving that the author has thought i8n through, as can the available information shown.  As for support, the author is friendly, with a good turnaround time on questions asked. Would be well worth the money at thrice the price. Highly recommended for both private and professional use - tho in particular the latter. It may be too powerful for quick "what to do today" notes.

Works very well with the Toodledo add on meaning can easily sync with two or more devices. Quick response from developer to queries. Hope he can develop the use of colour for Categories then will be 5* +
Love it. I agree the best on the market. Razor Max
Great app which I use all the time.

Super application with a great help menu. I needed to know how to create separate to-do lists. Simply create separate categories. Then filter by category and save the filter by a meaningful name. Click on the filter's category name and I've got my separate list. How easy is that?  Loving this app. Well worth every cent of the purchase price!

I am easily confused. I like the screen and it easily answers my question. Like can I repeat this for 1 hour every hour. Yes. Can i snooze. Yes. Even though it does a lot of things, somehow the separate smaller screens, are easy for me to understand and select. I am reviewing about 4 or 5 to do type lists at the moment. This 1 is winning!
The best of it's kind in the android market. Highly recommended.
Easy to use and very powerful

This app has served me well. I was using the Lite version on my Motorola Droid 2. I upgraded to the Pro version on my new Motorola Droid 4 and had problems with the import. Mike was prompt with the support and instructed me how to do the import. Thanks for a great app and service!
Saved me.  Love it.
This app is awesome. I was looking for a detailed manager for projects and also something that could be simple for day to day reminders. This fits the bill perfectly.
As if this app couldn't get any better, now we have the option to have a distinct ringtone for each task, no task app is better than this one!
Keeps getting better and better! Totally worth the paid version!
I have over 80 tasks and counting! I use it in my business every day. Mike is always very responsive with his technical support!

Also great follow-up response from the developer.
I love it. Must have A lot of features and customizations.
Very complete, tried many others, sticking with this one.

Easy to use and keeps me focused.

Great features. Just love it.

Super and very useful...I love it.
